<section xml:id="C9.S2">
<title>Differential Equation</title>         
<subsection xml:id="C9.S2.SS1">
<title>Airy’s Equation</title>             
<para xml:id="C9.S2.SS1.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="1" xml:id="C9.S2.SS1.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="9.2.1" mode="display" xml:id="C9.S2.E1">\frac{{\mathrm{d}}^{2}w}{{\mathrm{d}z}^{2}}=zw</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="2" xml:id="C9.S2.SS1.p1.s2">
All solutions are entire functions of <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C9.S2.SS1.p1.m1">z</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
  
<para xml:id="C9.S2.SS1.p2">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="3" xml:id="C9.S2.SS1.p2.s1">
Standard solutions are: <Math equation-number="9.2.2" mode="display" xml:id="C9.S2.E2">w=\mathrm{Ai}\left(z\right),\;\mathrm{Bi}\left(z\right),\;\mathrm{Ai}\left(ze^ {\mp 2\pi\mathrm{i}/3}\right)</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C9.S2.SS2">
<title>Initial Values</title>        
  
<para xml:id="C9.S2.SS2.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="4" xml:id="C9.S2.SS2.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="9.2.3" mode="display" xml:id="C9.S2.E3">\mathrm{Ai}\left(0\right)=\frac{1}{3^{2/3}\Gamma\left(\tfrac{2}{3}\right)}=0.3 5502\;80538\ldots,</Math> , <Math equation-number="9.2.4" mode="display" xml:id="C9.S2.E4">\mathrm{Ai}'\left(0\right)=-\frac{1}{3^{1/3}\Gamma\left(\tfrac{1}{3}\right)}=- 0.25881\;94037\ldots,</Math> , <Math equation-number="9.2.5" mode="display" xml:id="C9.S2.E5">\mathrm{Bi}\left(0\right)=\frac{1}{3^{1/6}\Gamma\left(\tfrac{2}{3}\right)}=0.6 1492\;66274\ldots,</Math> , <Math equation-number="9.2.6" mode="display" xml:id="C9.S2.E6">\mathrm{Bi}'\left(0\right)=\frac{3^{1/6}}{\Gamma\left(\tfrac{1}{3}\right)}=0.4 4828\;83573\ldots</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C9.S2.SS3">
<title>Numerically Satisfactory Pairs of Solutions</title>          
<para xml:id="C9.S2.SS3.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="5" xml:id="C9.S2.SS3.p1.s1">
Table 9.2.1 lists numerically satisfactory pairs of solutions of (9.2.1) for the stated intervals or regions; compare §2.7(iv).
</sentence>

</para>
         
<sentence sentence-num-in-section="6" xml:id="C9.S2.T1.s1">
Table 9.2.1: Numerically satisfactory pairs of solutions of Airy’s equation.
</sentence> 

